      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SHES A DELANEY (3) has been freshened since she drew poorly and worked in the Gold Tiara final but easily won a heat of that series prior. The only time she raced here she came from a wider barrier for fourth against the boys in the Sapling Stakes. She draws well and looks nicely placed. CANDY GIRL MARLEY (1) is a daughter of Somebeachsomewhere on debut for the strong Luke McCarthy stable. Close up in her latest trial and the inside draw is an aid to a first starter. Blake Fitzpatrick's Downbytheseaside debutant DECOUPAGE (7) draws wide but showed ability in beating CANDY GIRL MARLEY to win her latest trial. WALLABY WAY (8) draws wide but did a good job as runner-up from this barrier at Bathurst last start.",
